# COMMAND = [KEY ...]
# COMMAND += KEY ...
# The KEY can be:
#     - Just a char, like i, L, ", *
#     - CTRL-KEY sequence: ^k (CTRL-k), ^4
#     - ALT-KEY (meta) sequence: M-j (ALT-j), M-/
#     - Special keys: DOWN, UP
#                     LEFT, RIGHT
#                     HOME, END
#                     BACKSPACE
#                     INS, DEL
#                     ENTER
#                     PAGE_UP, PAGE_DOWN
#                     SPACE, TAB
#                     KEYPAD_CENTER
#                     ESCAPE
#                     F1 - F12
# The use of a digit as a KEY is deprecated.
# Maximum number of KEYs for one COMMAND is 5.
# Omitting the KEY for a COMMAND will unbind all its default keys.
# Individual default KEYs will be automatically unbound when they are explicitly bound to some other COMMAND.
# Meta-key detection is sensitive to the ESCDELAY environment variable. In its absence, MOC resets the default delay to 25ms.

